Not applicable. Model was given as in the question

2.3 Step 2: Path Diagram Construction

SEM Diagram

2.4 Step 3: Model Specification

  1. social on attitude
  2. social on exercise
  3. attitude on exercise (attitude as moderation between social and exercise)

model specification was named as exermodspec

exermodspec <- "
Exercise ~ c*social + b*attitude
attitude =~ A1 + A2
social =~ SP1 + SP2
attitude ~ a*social
ab := a*b
total := c + a*b
"

2.5 Step 4: Model Identification

a - pieces of information a=\(1/2\times\ k\times\left(k+1\right)+\)no of intercept k: no of item =19

b - free information b= no of factor loading - 1 + no of error variance + no of factor variance + no of factor covariance + no of intercept =12

Interpretation

standardized parameter

  1. Factor Loading
  • Attitude on A1: 0.649
  • Attitude on A2: 0.810
  • Social on SP1: 0.739
  • Social on SP2: 0.795
  1. Regression coefficient
  • Exercise on Social: 0.461
  • Exercise on Attitude: 0.238
  • Attitude on Social: 0.327

Mediation: both direct and indirect effect was significant, thus there was partial mediation effect present
